        "created_at": "2022-10-11T14:40:31.790Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Usually I have notifications turned off on my phone, because most messages I receive are not urgent and I don‚Äôt want to know about them until I check my phone in the evening or whenever.<br>\nBut of course every now and then there are messages that are in some sense time critical and therefore may not be answered in time by this strategy.<br>\nI wish there was an option for a sender of a message to set a hint that a message is time critical. And that the receiver could optionally configure (globally and possibly per contact) custom notification settings for messages with such a hint.</p>",
