        "name": "",
        "username": "Herohtar",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/herohtar/{size}/43780_2.png",
        "created_at": "2022-10-11T15:01:08.434Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I feel like this has been requested before, but didn‚Äôt immediately find the duplicate. However, here is a similar topic:</p><aside class=\"quote\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"2532\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/don42/48/1022_2.png\" class=\"avatar\">\n    <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/silent-low-priority-messages-to-avoid-disturbing-the-receiver-silent-messages/2532\">Silent, low priority messages to avoid disturbing the receiver (Silent messages)</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/feature-requests/17\"><span data-category-id=\"17\" style=\"--category-badge-color: #83B72A; --category-badge-text-color: #FFFFFF;\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category \" title=\"Post your ideas here for new features and functionality for the Signal app.\"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">Feature Requests</span></span></a>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    Hi, \nSometimes I like to send messages to people who I know are busy/sleeping \nat the moment and I want to avoid disturbing them. But I still want to send \nthe message now so the can answer when they have the time to look at \ntheir phones anyway. \nI imaging a flag set on the message to mark it as low priority and the receiving \napplication could then decide only to display a notification and not play a sound or \nvibrate. \nI‚Äôm not sure if this behavior would need to be configurable. \n\ndon\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n\n<p>As a workaround for this, you can create a new group chat with that person and designate it for ‚Äúemergency‚Äù messages and set the notifications to a different sound and/or to override Do Not Disturb, etc as desired. This works for a small number of contacts, but becomes very cumbersome if you want to make it available for more contacts/everyone.</p>",
