        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/o/e79b87/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-07-24T17:02:56.758Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I use notification profiles with Signal to only allow notifications at specific time window during the day. This helps me stay focused and only be bothered by notifications when I‚Äôm not busy and during the time of my choosing.</p>\n<p>However, there are times when messages have higher priority than usual. For group chats, we have <span class=\"mention\">@mentions</span>, which work great for this since there is an option to add exceptions for calls and for @ mentions. However, this is not possible for 1:1 chats.</p>\n<p>Currently, my solution to this has been to inform my contacts to just call me in case of urgent messages. However, calling can get inconvenient at times because there are situations where I can‚Äôt pick up a call and also when communicating with family and friends that live in different timezones. While you can just call so that they get a notification and then send the actual message as a regular chat message, I fell like it would be better to have a dedicated feature for this.</p>\n<p>My proposed solution for this is to have @ mentions be available for 1:1 chats. Since they are already implemented for groups and have an exception option already in notification profiles, adding this feature should not require as much of a change.</p>\n<p>Thanks.</p>",
